,"D892417F-5570-4940-A311-AA918B8A2AF7","DAFC9825-B67E-4FF5-8E6C-4D05CC20E554","DBC40A27-66D6-4C9D-927E-1D5F05092F1A","E431262C-0AE0-4E4B-9DA4-A2E35B49E671","E687FCD9-066C-4E47-8B6C-164C1B586A18","E72F7052-876D-476F-89A0-9AEE369F0317","EC9276F5-8C4A-431C-882B-4BA90A9D8881","ECA6DAA1-1E5C-4D1F-8186-B9969A5E9EAD","ED5C21DE-D335-4D82-85CF-485CD449C602","EEF9E8C9-3899-4E76-8A11-C2265812FA53","F2A935D9-8E28-4421-8382-837E3E0E99B7","FCDD2204-2B10-4061-8CDF-928C5DE4C24D","FD36A9C3-DDBD-43BF-BA4B-AE2D2C8CA87F","FE996429-CEFA-41FC-8228-3E4661406DDF"],"areaId":"c13a7bec43d76341eb66c54f4db9d788c61998e3c5c6b67951853c090ae9b37b","forecaster":"Kreston Rohrig","issueDateTime":"2026-04-15T22:30:00Z","expiryDateTime":"2026-04-16T22:30:00Z","isTranslated":false,"isAutoTranslated":false,"isMultiDay":false,"timezone":"America\/Denver","weatherSummary":{"days":[]},"snowpackSummary":{"days":[]},"avalancheSummary":{"days":[{"date":"2026-04-16T22:30:00Z","content":"<p>Avalanche conditions are generally safe. In very steep or extreme terrain, use caution around newly drifted snow and watch for small sluffs. Even a small amount of moving snow can knock you off your feet and carry you into hazardous terrain further down the mountain.<\/p><hr><p><em>Researchers Ian McCammon and Sara Boilen are developing new tools for managing human factors for&nbsp;backcountry skiers and boarders. This survey asks about personal experiences with human factors and will take 7 - 8 minutes to fill out. <\/em><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https:\/\/eoustmhs.qualtrics.com\/jfe\/form\/SV_exIaG7ZwFaA9lOK\"><em>Link is&nbsp;HERE.<\/em><\/a><em> Thank you for your help!<\/em><\/p>"}]},"terrainAndTravelAdvice":{"days":[[],[],[]]},"communication":{"headline":"","sms":""},"media":{"Images":[{"id":"a9d45854-eb92-445a-9880-23c5feb3932e","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1776196313\/AvIDfx\/w7owhjq9hvvu8ktbrvqp.webp","width":2500,"height":3333,"credit":"","caption":"<p>If riding in steep terrain like this, manage your sluff so you don't get knocked down or swept into consequential terrain features.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"Small sluff in steep gulley","dateTaken":"2026-04-14T19:51:59.173Z","isArchived":false},{"id":"e285ecc6-c15b-440f-bf53-62eedbf2fc60","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1776284999\/AvIDfx\/zkx1xgh2w2lbumle1l9e.webp","width":1600,"height":1200,"credit":"","caption":"<p>Drifted areas of snow look smooth and rounded. Recent areas of drifted snow were observed just below ridgelines. If you see cracking in the new snow at you feet you have found a drifted area and need to assess the steep terrain you plan to ride. Think about the consequences of taking even just a small ride. <\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"An avalanche with tracks nearby","dateTaken":"2026-04-15T19:29:19.513Z","isArchived":false},{"id":"a9d631e6-e571-4eda-8680-ee513dc49e83","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1776284648\/AvIDfx\/bj02qo0bsoexugvocmvm.webp","width":512,"height":384,"credit":"","caption":"<p>This small slab of denser snow was observed on Wednesday near Berthoud Pass Though it's LOW (1 of 5) danger, small avalanches can be triggered in the recently drifted snow. These avalanche are only consequential if you get knocked off your feet and tumble down the slope.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"A small avalanche in steep terrain.","dateTaken":"2026-04-15T17:54:44Z","isArchived":false},{"id":"cbfcfedd-e5fd-4b60-9f85-ef12f77086ce","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1776285028\/AvIDfx\/fdoxahthwq7tiossramj.webp","width":2500,"height":3333,"credit":"","caption":"<p>Warming temperatures in the coming days could further contribute to avalanche activity. Morning dry snow may become moist and increasingly sensitive to triggering as it settles throughout the day, potentially resulting in slow-moving wet slides initiated at your feet. Watch for signs of bunching or cohesion in the dry snow; if you notice this, be prepared for the possibility of triggering a small avalanche on steep slopes.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"A ski track leading into a small wind slab avalanche in terrain that appears steep, shallow, and rocky","dateTaken":"2026-04-15T20:01:54.418Z","isArchived":false}]},"dangerRatings":{"days":[{"position":1,"alp":"low","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-16T22:30:00Z"},{"position":2,"alp":"low","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-17T22:30:00Z"},{"position":3,"alp":"low","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-18T22:30:00Z"}]},"avalancheProblems":{"days":[[{"type":"windSlab","aspectElevations":["n_alp","ne_alp","e_alp"],"likelihood":"unlikely","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"1.5"}}],[{"type":"windSlab","aspectElevations":["n_alp","ne_alp","e_alp"],"likelihood":"unlikely","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"1.5"}}],[{"type":"windSlab","aspectElevations":["n_alp","ne_alp","e_alp"],"likelihood":"unlikely","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"1.5"}}]]}},{"id":"6ab14212-90ab-4b79-9c46-b7996aa7b139","publicName":"10-11-12-17-18-19-20-21-24-25-37-38-39-4-40-41-5-56-9","type":"avalancheforecast","polygons":["07217D33-65CD-450C-870A-EC2693445190","0FAA4D28-2B56-40A5-A79C-E534A07D98ED","184B517E-9DEF-44B4-9EA8-E45CC96DB776","2CADF229-A5B1-420C-9A58-0D72FE71FDCD","2D929612-B1FD-4AC4-BA12-494ADDCBB442","389E01FC-0600-42E2-82FF-BEF3B23C6105","3C27CD1A-FD13-48B3-B0FF-A5947832FBEB","3F69D3A0-1915-4E8E-AB3F-8F3961B64F10","4481315B-A3B2-430F-AD25-51F077D30A1A","49B9973C-4E52-4B70-A4A9-4718AFB95868","4ADCB7E9-CFDB-462F-B6FB-E787CF1EA2C6","5AD4C8BF-731F-4B70-8A78-C3D3151A85DD","61E64E4C-03E7-433B-B273-22BF6C97E026","B65805C7-DE42-4F35-BDEE-14E7D6B7605A","C835BE8E-EC55-4C2B-8B52-815C66D0209C","E4DE90A5-20FE-4A8F-B297-163BA41C19C9","EEE05A8E-51CF-4AF4-9509-EC7C64D14D20","F9BD77AC-C360-47DF-8195-D16A4C65DE30","FCEB8EE2-B8A0-44E8-ABD9-EEED4EDDDAA7"],"areaId":"2d5d4e1c9b2b0bea2a120839fdef58070d0d6287513f4